            <span id="First_Paragraph_Mod">
            In Hawaii we were living in a house, which was better than what we had in Hong Kong. It was a wooden house, and guess what? The house had a lot of holes in it. When we took a shower, we had so many holes in the shower room, we had to turn off the light. You know why? A lot of teenage guys around that area would creep underneath our house and peek at us when we were taking a shower. We were so scared that we had to turn off the light so that nobody could see us, and we had to take showers in the dark. The whole house was basically saturated with termites. Every night when we went to sleep, the termite powder dropped onto our faces and sometimes into our mouths. You could not walk without making noises in that house.
            <br />
            </span>
            <div id="boxmodex3" class="clearfix">
