            The saddest moments that I have had in life were when I lost my first husband and when I lost my second husband. When a person grows into adulthood, they feel that they have power; they feel that they are have power to run the world, to give to the world, to manipulate the world, or to have a future. It’s kind of like building a home and building a bubble. When I saw the bubble burst, I saw that my children had no father and my youngest one was only six months old. 
