            It was difficult for me after he died. I had to go back to training. I lost about 30 pounds. I had pain, so much pain that it took me five years to forget. During this time I began to understand and realize that the Mormon Church is the only true church, because after reading all the scriptures, I understood how everything could be true and how the doctrine of the Mormon Church is so close to the New Testament and the Old Testament. There’s no other church that I know of that even resembles or gets anywhere close to what the New Testament is talking about, what Jesus was talking about. Only the Mormon Church is very close in the doctrines. The combination of all that strengthened my faith in the Church. <br /><br />

            I went back to the Church. Right before my husband died, he also learned about the gospel and was baptized. He couldn’t get endowed because he was too sick to go to the temple. Five years after he died I met my second husband, and I told him, “Right now I have devoted my life to God. I will be a missionary, and if you don’t plan to be a missionary with me, I don’t want to marry you.” He said, “Yes. I will be a missionary with you.” Without knowing whether he was for real or not, I wrote down on a big, big piece of paper and made him sign it. And he signed that paper. So we got married, and he got baptized. At that point I was very happy. I was the Relief Society President in the Oakland Ward. Things were going well. I was attending the temple regularly. <br />
