                I began to understand people. I understand why they are hurt, why they are sad. It was an invaluable experience and lesson for me. That adverse event brought me closer to God, made me understand his pain when he was in Gethsemane, and made me understand how to be a better disciple. <br /><br /> 

                At this moment in time, Norman is still not very active in the church, but he’s trying his best to come back. He has his own journey, which I don’t know, but I can say that I was very fortunate. After he came back to the family, we had other hurdles that we had to cross.
                </span>
